Japan's Olympus Optical Co. Ltd. announced Wednesday  a consolidated pre-tax loss of 245 million yen (2.4 million dollars) for the  year to March, reversing a profit of 10.4 billion yen a year earlier.
The leading camera manufacturer said worldwide sales fell more than 10  percent during the same period to 240 billion yen.
Olympus forecast a return to the black in the current year with pre-tax  earnings of seven billion yen on increased sales of 257 billion yen.
